# Spartan Test TODO

Current roadmap. Completed, cancelled, duplicated, and historical items remain available
in Git history instead of being mixed into the active list.

Parser and syntax:
 ☐ Support complete multi-line PHP syntax in `; code ...` definition blocks
 ☐ Allow function and class definitions without the `;` prefix
 ☐ Redesign critical-test syntax; current `!expr` conflicts with PHP's logical-not operator
 ☐ Design conditional test sections that can be enabled again later in the file
 ☐ Add a concise JSON API request syntax, including `POST-JS $uri $data`

Execution control:
 ☐ Add `STest::once($period)` for running an unchanged test once per period
 ☐ Let `STest::once()` include source class modification times in its cache key
 ☐ Add `STest::failOnce($period)` to suppress repeated reports for unchanged failures
 ☐ Add CLI controls for once/fail-once state: enable, reset, and ignore
 ☐ Generalize temporary suspension beyond the existing dated `STest::stop()`
 ☐ Allow temporary suppression of failure reporting while still executing the test
 ☐ Pass additional arguments from `stest-all` to every selected test
 ☐ Add `stest-all --realm` as a standard forwarded option
 ☐ Allow controlled GNU Parallel arguments through `stest-all`
 ☐ Design explicit environments/tiers (`dvp`, `test`, `prod`) selected by CLI or config
 ☐ Allow host, domain, and other test settings to vary by environment/tier
 ☐ Support critical tests that run first and abort the suite when they fail
 ☐ Support tests that must not execute in parallel

Tags and selection:
 ☐ List all defined tags with test counts
 ☐ Evaluate hierarchical tags, e.g. `db.mongo` also matching `db`
 ☐ Map changed source files to dependent tests, not only recently changed test files

Comparison and output:
 ☐ Show focused colored diffs for added, removed, and changed result sections
 ☐ Improve smart string and nested array comparisons
 ☐ Add relational result checks such as `~ > $value` and related operators
 ☐ Add XPath result assertions for HTML/XML values
 ☐ Show timing for individual test expressions
 ☐ Optionally record the last successful run time and server in test metadata

Web and API testing:
 ☐ Add parallel URL execution syntax such as `/[$urls]`
 ☐ Add first-class JSON API tests and assertions
 ☐ Expand response assertions for headers, redirects, cookies, XPath, and generic errors
 ☐ Improve parameter parsing for application dispatch integrations

Reporting and alerts:
 ☐ Add hooks for first failure, per-test failure, and success
 ☐ Add configurable alert destinations and routing rules
 ☐ Support script, URL, Slack, Discord, Telegram, and Twilio destinations
 ☐ Add alert spam control, temporary suppression, priorities, and escalation
 ☐ Add remote JSON reporting for runs, failures, and critical errors
 ☐ Add `--error-as-alert`

Automation and coverage:
 ☐ Build an inotify-based runner that executes tests when source files change
 ☐ Use `get_included_files()` to map tests to their source dependencies
 ☐ Generate or update a test skeleton from a class and its methods
 ☐ Report class methods without test coverage
 ☐ Add a git-push test-server workflow
 ☐ Add cron/inotify orchestration for once-per-period and dependency-based runs

Configuration and architecture:
 ☐ Evaluate YAML configuration with local overrides and parent inheritance
 ☐ Split instance creation from configuration responsibilities
 ☐ Evaluate renaming `STest::$DOMAIN` to `STest::$HOST`
 ☐ Separate error-handler modes for test evaluation and reporting
 ☐ Support configurable discovery/parallel options without exposing unsafe shell input

Maintenance:
 ☐ Review examples and remove obsolete or intentionally broken files from normal docs
 ☐ Consolidate and improve user documentation
